.TH "LIGHTNING-WALLET-IMPORT-SEED" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-wallet-import-seed \- import a wallet from seed words
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning wallet-import-seed
.I wallet_name seed_words
.SH DESCRIPTION
Creates a new wallet entry initialized from the provided seed words.
Returns an error if the wallet already exists.
.PP
Output:
.nf
{"status":"imported","wallet":"<name>"}
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-wallet-seed-verify (1),
.BR lightning-wallet-list (1)
